The Unusual Pet Vets is a group of exotic animal veterinarians based in Australia. We have a number of exotic-only clinics and see a range of animals including reptiles, birds, guinea pigs, rabbits, ferrets, rats, mice and frogs. 

We started our YouTube channel as a way to share information, instructional videos and interesting cases.

For more information please see our website (www.unusualpetvets.com.au), follow us on facebook (www.facebook.com/theunusualpetvets) or check us out on instagram (www.instagram.com/theunusualpetvets)!

description:
Hello friends,
Thank you for stopping by and checking my channel.
I started playing basketball when I was about 7 years old. I played ball for years until my early 20's. But then I started playing less and less as I got older. Almost 30 years without playing basketball. But when I turned 50 I decided to give it another try. In March 4, 2017 I started practicing basketball again although it is mostly on the weekends. I feel great when I play basketball and if everything goes well, I will continue to play for many years to come.  
It is never too late to enjoy your favorite sport, even at 50. If I can do it, you can do it too!
I want to thank you for watching the videos.
PS: And yes, I really like Double Rims :)

description:
This is Juice WRLD's official channel.

Chicago-area hip-hop musician Juice WRLD delivers introspective lyrics atop melodic production, echoing Travis Scott and Post Malone. Born Jarad Higgins in 1998, the Calumet Park artist grew up playing piano, drums, and guitar, turning to rap freestyling in high school. Influenced by rock music and Chicago drill from Lil Durk and Chief Keef, Higgins began recording as Juice TheKidd, a moniker derived from his haircut, which resembled 2Pac's in the film Juice.

His early tracks were all posted online, leading up to 2017's Juice WRLD 999 EP. Produced by Nick Mira and Sidepce, the set included the singles "Lucid Dreams (Forget Me)" and "All Girls Are the Same". Both tracks would also land on his official debut full-length album, Goodbye & Good Riddance, which peaked at number 15 on the Billboard 200 upon release in May 2018.

description:
Mostly testing games I‚Äôm interested in, from a somewhat technical point of view, because if there‚Äôs something I enjoy and love about PC gaming is flexibility and customization in our games, and tweak stuff to make them run as good as possible given certain hardware specs.

Videos have Timestamps, feel free to jump to the section you want to see.

PC Specs will always be in the video Description.

I'm left handed, so I tend to put a lot on emphasis on keybinds and control setups, even if I'm playing a particular game with Gamepad, it's still important to check those Controls.

I don't do requests, I play/test what I enjoy, there's always too many games coming out, no time for everything :P

These videos aren't "reviews", more like first "technical" impressions and Basic Testing, tweaking Settings if necessary.

Stick to English for the comments, I can answer stuff in Spanish too, but yeah best to stick to what most people understand.

Hope you enjoy your stay : )

As the world's largest production house and tourism content archive of factual 4K UHD video from South Asia, you can make us part of your production plans in India/South Asia. We deliver the widest range of production, gear, location, support services and stock footage.

description:
This is a gaming channel‚Äî I like playing retro-style games, mostly RPGs and 2d action.
I'm also fond of things Japanese, and I translate some of the things I like.
Currently I'm working on Phantasy Star Portable 2 Infinity of which I'll upload videos as I go.
I mostly upload challenging gameplay videos, right now I'm playing: Grim Dawn, Path of Exile, Hollow Knight, Cuphead and the occasional indie game that catches my eye.
In the future I plan to create content of some Japanese-only games with on-the-fly English translations so you can watch and understand some games that were never released in the west.

Personally I don't like some guy yakking away all the time when I just want to enjoy the gameplay and music when watching other videos, so my videos focus on the games themselves. 
I have a pretty beefy computer, so I record everything in 1080p 60 FPS.

So if you enjoy watching games, check some of my stuff out. Perhaps you'll discover a game you like.

In 2008 we radically altered our business approach, creating a bespoke, purpose-built showroom which successfully married the very latest instore experience with our staff's unrivalled level of photographic knowledge and customer care.

description:
When I was a young boy (1950's), I learned to play golf by closely watching the best players at the course I grew up on. I would then stand in front of a window and copy their swings... then I would go to the practice area to ingrain that look and new feeling to muscle memory. That WAS and STILL IS a great way to learn! It's called SELF-DISCOVERY! 

When you discover a helpful motion or thought ALL BY YOURSELF, YOU WILL NEVER FORGET IT! - I never have!  

At the age of 78, I'm still a mid single-digit player. My goal with this YouTube channel is to provide a platform for TEACHING and LEARNING! I will provide videos and detailed descriptions of the finest golfers in the world, their swings and some of their finest shots so YOU can learn and improve as I have. 

The focus here is geared toward TEACHING and LEARNING the short game (putting, chipping, pitching and wedge play from 120-yards in), but you will also see some of the finest, Tour-Proven full swings and descriptions as well.‚õ≥Ô∏è

description:
Aditya Varma is a director of photography and photographer from Mumbai.
His two full length feature films, 'Namdev Bhau in Search of Silence' (dir. Daria Gai) and 'Kia and Cosmos' (dir. Sudipto Roy),  Both of the films have  travelled to various international film festivals and he was nominated for best cinematography in Milan and Nice International Fim Festivals for 'Kia and Cosmos'. 
He has also been the stills photographer for 'Manto' (dir. Nandita Das), which was showcased at Cannes Film Festival in Un Certain Regard section. He has shot and edited over twenty advertisements for leading companies and fashion campaigns for national and international brands including promotionals for Bumble, Netflix, Jio. He shot music videos for musicians like Prateek Kuhad, Ritviz, Jasleen Royal, Vayu, Hanita Bhambri. He shoots documentaries as well, the most recent of which is a travel show following leading bikers of India called "Cruising Legends". He is currently working on a web series.

description:
Turns out that I wasn't rendering my videos correctly. I was leaving extraneous frames left over from interpolation in pretty much all my videos and also the my output FPS was slightly off. So I decided I would redo all my videos since there's not that many and only a few have a lot of views. This time I will make sure to not make these dumb mistakes.
I am going to stick to 60 FPS because that's the most common refresh rate on current monitors and TVs.
The 4 primary software I will be using will be Sony Vegas 12, GoPro Studio, Hybrid and Freemake Video converter.
I believe in HFR for all video content. Message me if you want to see any particular video at a higher frame rate!
